  <front>
    <title>DHCP Auto-configure Option (Option code 116) Deprecated</title>
    <author fullname="Ralph Droms" initials="R." surname="Droms">
      <organization>Cisco Systems</organization>
    </author>
    <date year="2002" month="May" day="14"/>
    <abstract>
      <t>RFC2563 defines the DHCP Auto-configure option, which controls whether a DHCP client uses address auto-configuration. Because of the potential threat of a denial of service attack, the use of RFC2563 is deprecated.</t>
    </abstract>
